      {
        "id": "ec2e8860c202f6d971cadf178820d5e453b9d63b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-07 11:20:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nYuriy, if the artifact is only relevany for VF/PNF and not VL CP etc I'd rather to keep it like it is now.\n\nI also wanted to make sure you understand the difference between resource and resource instance: do we need CDS artifacts in both cases?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "a275ccaac57872a52cb305d0196e3a030637e39f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4567,
          "name": "Yuriy Malakov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "yuriy.malakov@att.com",
          "username": "ym9479"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-07 11:28:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n\nOfir, i'm fine with just having for PNF/VF for Dublin release. All the CDS Artifacts are attached to the PNF/VF INSTANCE LEVEL AS FOLLOWS IN THE CSAR:  \n\nC:\\Users\\YM9479\\Desktop\\NEW\\Artifacts\\Deployment\\CONTROLLER_BLUEPRINT_ARCHIVE\\TEST1\n\nC:\\Users\\YM9479\\Desktop\\NEW\\Artifacts\\Resources\\testpnf1400\\Deployment\\CONTROLLER_BLUEPRINT_ARCHIVE\\TEST2.CBA\n\nC:\\Users\\YM9479\\Desktop\\NEW\\Artifacts\\Resources\\testpnf1600\\Deployment\\CONTROLLER_BLUEPRINT_ARCHIVE\\TEST3.CBA\n\nCan you define resource and resource instance",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "1fd72f6bfffb33c48ac7b09f89d08566e1ab7f42",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-07 12:44:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nResource is any VF/PNF as a building block, once dragged & dropped to a service composition, it becomes a resource instance.\n\nAny definitions (hence properties, artifacts) that are part of the resource are automatically inherited to the resource instance level, but not the other way around.\n\nQuestion is, should a CDS artifact be generated per a VF/PNF, or maybe it might change within instances of the same VF/PNF inside different services?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "f6eba55a7a89170bc684ade05e5523e56fa03b12",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4567,
          "name": "Yuriy Malakov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "yuriy.malakov@att.com",
          "username": "ym9479"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-07 12:53:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nExcellent question, i could see the need for both use case. The 80%/20% rule will be that the CBA artifact is part of the model that is reusable across all service for VF/PNF. However, the 20% of use case that might require a customization of the CBA Artifact for a given VF/PNF within a service.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "2d8f616f9789355c6daeb4859ca2a7c0fb0cb7f2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-08 10:42:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI'm not sure an artifact can be overridden at the instance level. Maybe you should consider attaching it only at the instance level? That way you can achieve both default and customized artifact, depends on CDS internal logic.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "9779cd04dcff0311354b4671c10f8ccd409a6d01",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4567,
          "name": "Yuriy Malakov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "yuriy.malakov@att.com",
          "username": "ym9479"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-08 20:24:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nOfir, we can consider this as a future enhancement post Dublin. For Dublin release, we are good with just importing/uploading the CBA artifact at resource level for VF/PNF.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "aba42589d18090cb2fddfe8b48f812ea68195540",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
